Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Triadimefon in Organic Solvents at Temperatures between (288.15 and 333.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: Using a laser monitoring technique, the solubility of triadimefon in acetonitrile, hexane, heptane, cyclohexane, methylbenzene, and 1,4-dimethylbenzene was measured at temperatures from (288.15 to 333.15) K at a pressure of 0.1 MPa. The experimental data were well-correlated with the modified Apelblat equation and the ?h model.
